<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="379" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d379">
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                                </head>
                                <p>No official record of the substance of this conversation has been
                                    found. The information set forth above is derived from the Log,
                                        <pb facs="0783" n="697" xml:id="pg_697"/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_532">p. 532</ref>,
                                    which adds that the meeting lasted until 12:30 a.m. Elliott
                                    Roosevelt (pp. 113–114) indicates that from what little he
                                    overheard of the meeting, the subject of discussion was the de
                                    Gaulle-Giraud controversy.</p>
                            </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>